    • onItemImported

      public void onItemImported​(java.io.File source, int objId, java.lang.String destArcPath, long millis, int reportControl, java.lang.Exception ex)
      Called during import to notify about a processed item.
      Parameters:
      source - Processed file (or directory).
      objId - Object ID of imported item.
      destArcPath - Archive path or name of imported item.
      millis - Duration of processing.
      reportControl - Bitset of constants that describe whether the file was imported, skipped, etc.
      ex - Exception object in case of an error. Otherwise null.
